# No em dash (U+2014)

**Never** write the em dash character U+2014 in any project text. Not in site copy, i18n, blog posts, comments, docs, rules, commit messages, or agent replies.

## Use instead

| Context | Use |
|---------|-----|
| Title or label separator | Hyphen with spaces: `Blog - Kilometer 0 Digital` |
| Contrast or clarification | Comma: `services, not another provider` |
| List item label | Colon or hyphen: `Marketing: km0digital.com` or `Smoke - PASS` |
| Parenthetical aside | Commas or parentheses |

## Examples

```text
// BAD (uses U+2014 between clauses)
Open services [em dash] not another provider.
Blog [em dash] Kilometer 0 Digital

// GOOD
Open services, not another provider.
Blog - Kilometer 0 Digital
```

Before finishing any edit under `src/`, run a quick check: search for U+2014 (`grep $'\xe2\x80\x94' -r src/` or `rg $'\u2014' src/`) and confirm zero matches.

Validation also runs automatically on `npm run dev`, `npm run build`, git pre-commit (after `./scripts/install-git-hooks.sh`), and GitHub Actions CI.
